{#- Legal page template — Wave 4C.1 migration.
    Extends the shared site base; injects the verbatim legal body from
    render/site/content/legal_body.html (frozen by SHA-256 baseline at
    render/site/harness/baselines/legal-body-sha256.txt).

    Per Mara's pressure-test recommendation: the legal prose body is
    NOT transformed by Jinja — passed through with `| safe` so HTML
    entities, em-dashes, and clause structure render identically to
    pre-migration. The chrome (head + nav + footer) updates to the
    shared site standard, which adds the 5-item public nav + Legal
    footer link. Those chrome additions are intentional per the Wave 4
    consistency goal and explicitly not a regression.
-#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block title %}Legal — Soterra Labs{% endblock %}
{% block description %}Soterra Labs terms of service and privacy policy.{% endblock %}
{% block canonical %}https://soterralabs.ai/legal/{% endblock %}

{% block style_link %}
<style>
{{ legal_inline_css | safe }}
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
{{ legal_body | safe }}
{% endblock %}
